HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 282
BY REPRESENTATIVES CHANCE HENRY AND CHASSION
A RESOLUTION
To create the Task Force on Utility Terrain Vehicles (UTVs) to study the feasibility of
implementing safety regulations regarding UTVs.
WHEREAS, some UTVs are capable of going upwards of sixty miles per hour; and
WHEREAS, UTVs can be made street legal and travel on public roads alongside
motor vehicles; and
WHEREAS, the UTV market rose above ten billion dollars in 2025; and
WHEREAS, the Consumer Federation of America reported seventy-eight UTV
fatalities in 2024.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby establish and provide for the Task Force on Utility
Terrain Vehicles to study laws and regulations for the safe operation of utility terrain
vehicles and to provide recommendations or proposals for legislation.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that any recommendations or proposals shall be
submitted by written report to the House Committee on Transportation, Highways and
Public Works and to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S.
24:772 before the convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
members:
(1) The superintendent of Louisiana State Police or his designee.
(2) The executive director of Louisiana Sheriffs' Association or his designee.
(3) The executive director of Louisiana Association of Chiefs of Police or his
designee.
(4) The secretary of the Department of Transportation and Development or his
designee.
(5) The executive director of the Louisiana Highway Safety Commission or his
designee.
