(6) The commissioner of the office of motor vehicles or his designee.
(7) The commissioner of the Department of Insurance or his designee.
(8) The state fire marshal or his designee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that at the first meeting, the members shall elect a
chairman and other officers as the task force may deem appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene its first meeting no
later than August 1, 2026, and once every two months thereafter.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force constitutes a quorum
for the transaction of business and all official actions of the task force require the affirmative
vote of a majority of the members.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which they may be
individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that meetings of the task force are subject to the
Open Meetings Law, R.S. 42:11 et seq., and records of the task force are subject to the
Public Records Law, R.S. 44:1 et seq.
